MODULE: src/routes
FILES: 1
RESPONSIBILITY: HTTP API route definitions — chat, SSE events, session binding, screenshots, system exec
INTERFACES:
- createApiRouter({realtimeHub, sessionBind, messageRouter, sessionStore}): Router
- POST /api/bind: bind web session to Telegram chat ID
- POST /api/unbind: remove session binding
- GET /api/bindings: query bindings (all or by webSessionId)
- GET /api/events: SSE stream with message history replay on connect
- POST /api/chat: send message via unified messageRouter
- POST /api/chat/reset: clear session state
- POST /api/screenshot: capture screenshot
- POST /api/system/exec: execute system command
KEY_FILES:
- api-routes.js: All API endpoints (~200 lines)
DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: express: Router
- imports: src/services/chat-service.js: buildSessionContext (for SSE key building)
- imports: src/services/screenshot-service.js: captureScreenshot
- imports: src/services/system-exec-service.js: executeSystemCommand
TRAPS:
- All F-018 endpoints (bind/unbind/bindings/chat/reset) call await sessionBind.ensureReady() — must await before calling sync methods
- /api/events replays full message history on connect (AC6 offline sync) — could be large for long sessions
- No authentication on bind/unbind endpoints (consistent with project pattern but security concern for production)
UPDATED: 2026-03-22
